Note: Before using this app, please create an index with name "centurion". 
In case you need help in creating index,please refer to https://docs.splunk.com/Documentation/Splunk/8.1.3/Indexer/Setupmultipleindexes
 

This application is developed to bring multiple threat intelligence sharing platform, 
also known as IOC feed vendor, together under one roof. The application will help security professionals in threat hunting of IP addresses by looking at 
their reputation against multiple threat sharing platforms.


Install this app on your search head and happy theat hunting. To get the user guide go to "$SPLUNK_HOME$/etc/apps/Centurion/appserver/static/CENTURION.pdf".

At this moment supported IOC is IP Address, but soon will update the app to include URL and Hash. Also, will keep on adding more providers. So, 
if you do not find your favourite IOC vendors do let us know (splunk@qostechnology.in) and we promise to add the same in our next release.

Supported Information providers:
1. Abuseip
2. AlienVault
3. Antideo
4. Apilityio
5. Badip
6. Blacklist
7. BlackListMaster
8. Cymon
9. Dshield
10. FraudGaurd
11. HetrixTools
12. IBM X-force
13. IPDataCo
14. IPStack
15. Moochersip
16. Mon
17. Neutrino
18. threatCrowd
19. VirusTotal
20. VoidAPI
21. VoxProx

